China Mobile Rises Most in 2 Weeks After Adding RIM’s BlackBerry

-- B y   B e l i n d a   C a o
-- 
2011-09-06T15:33:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-06/china-mobile-rises-most-in-2-weeks-after-adding-rim-s-blackberry.html
China Mobile Ltd. (941) , the world’s
biggest phone carrier by subscribers, rose the most in two weeks
after Research In Motion Ltd. introduced the first BlackBerry
smartphone that will work on the Chinese operator’s homegrown
wireless network.  The company’s American depositary receipts advanced 1.6
percent to $50.25 at 11:29 a.m. New York time, the biggest
intraday increase since Aug. 23.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Belinda Cao in New York at 
 lcao4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
